Warb.Inst. Parable of Sower. Woodcut. Christ preaching from the ship & (in background). Parable of the Sower from Ludolphus, Leven ons Heeren, Antwerp, Leeuw [sic], 1487, ca. 1181. [Arthur M.] Hind, Hist. of Woodcut, II, [London: Constable, 1935] 567, 323; [notitie in potlood onleesbaar]; Icarus, drawing by Hans Bol, signed and dated 1573, Sale Paris 11-4-1924, photo Netherl. Art Inst.L. n°3030. Ploughman on right, sheperd looking up on left, & drawing (reversed) for the engraving- in the engraving now shown at top (the engraving repr. in Henkel, Ovid.Met., Abb. 50 [= Max D. Henkel, 'Illustrierte Ausgaben von Ovids Metamorphosen im XV., XVI. und XVII. Jahrhundert', in: Vorträge der Bibliothek Warburg 6 (1926-1927), pp. 58-144]; [Kantlijn]: Daedalus flying, Icarus falling down.
